ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported
1= catch, trials trying to catch careless responding for quality control purposes; 2= two weeks; 3= one month; 4= one year; 5= ten years

ElementDescription: Trial Counter for a particular trial type
Value for the present choice (Value for the future choice is always $1000)

Discounting factor 'k' computed for the present trial (or boolean correct [0,1] for catch trials): k = [(a/v)-1]/d; a = future value ($1000); v = current value, computed as present value adjusted; d = delay in days
Notes: k = [(a/v)-1]/d; a = future value ($1000) ; v = current value, computed as present value adjusted; d = delay in days
1= timeout, no response until timeout; 2= mouseup, pointerup.mouse, mouse click; 3= touchend, pointerup.touch, touchscreen touch

ElementDescription: Time (in months) it takes for value to halve, computed as inverse of average of final Ks over all delays.
Average reaction time of all trials (ms)
Median reaction time of all trials (ms)
Standard deviation of reaction times of all trials (ms)
Natual logarithm of the average of all Ks
